<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="374" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1754,2006]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="374" pageId="7" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1754,1779]" pageId="7" pageNumber="373">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[280,482,1754,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pierella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boliviana" status="stat. nov.">
<emphasis box="[280,482,1754,1779]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="373">Pierella boliviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[488,594,1754,1779]" pageId="7" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[488,594,1754,1779]" pageId="7" pageNumber="373">stat. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1793" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1793" box="[720,996,1754,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pierella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luna">
<emphasis box="[720,793,1754,1779]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="373">P. luna</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius" box="[811,988,1754,1779]" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1793) Entomologia systematica emendata et aucta. Secundum classes, ordines, genera, species adjectis synonimis, locis, observationibus, descriptionibus. Vol. 3. Hafniae, Christian Gottlieb Proft, 488 pp." type="book" year="1793">
Fabricius, 
<number box="[931,988,1755,1779]" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" value="1793.0">1793</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in size (male FW length: 
<quantity box="[1286,1406,1755,1779]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.85" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" unit="mm" value="38.5" valueMax="39.0" valueMin="38.0">38–39 mm</quantity>
[n = 
<number box="[173,189,1791,1815]" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" value="3.0">3</number>
]; female FW length: 
<quantity box="[427,547,1791,1815]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" unit="mm" value="40.0" valueMax="42.0" valueMin="38.0">38–42 mm</quantity>
[n = 
<number box="[606,621,1791,1815]" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" value="3.0">3</number>
]) and HW shape, but the ocelli of 
<taxonomicName box="[1005,1082,1790,1815]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pierella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luna">
<emphasis box="[1005,1082,1790,1815]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="373">P. luna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are restricted to Rs-M 
<number box="[1332,1340,1805,1819]" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" value="1.0">1</number>
and M 
<number box="[1419,1427,1805,1819]" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" value="1.0">1</number>
- M 
<number box="[176,184,1844,1858]" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" value="2.0">2</number>
. Within the “ 
<taxonomicName box="[337,429,1829,1854]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pierella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamia">
<emphasis box="[337,429,1829,1854]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="373">P. lamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group”, 
<taxonomicName box="[618,752,1829,1854]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pierella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boliviana" status="stat. nov.">
<emphasis box="[618,752,1829,1854]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="373">P. boliviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[759,867,1829,1854]" pageId="7" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[759,867,1829,1854]" pageId="7" pageNumber="373">stat. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[1101,1193,1829,1854]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pierella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamia">
<emphasis box="[1101,1193,1829,1854]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="373">P. lamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from that by the straight HW costal margin and the outer margin projected at M 
<number box="[939,947,1883,1897]" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" value="1.0">1</number>
. There are four incomplete ocelli on VHW, but some individuals might have a reduced ocellus in M 
<number box="[788,796,1922,1936]" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" value="2.0">2</number>
-M 
<number box="[829,837,1922,1936]" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" value="3.0">3</number>
. VHW post-discal and postmedian lines are straight. Androconial patch is characterized by a well-marked, elongated dark central area (
<figureCitation box="[1098,1183,1945,1970]" captionStart="FIGURES 29 – 35" captionStartId="5.[151,264,998,1021]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,274,970]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[150,1436,267,977]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 29 – 35. Hind wings androconial patches in dorsal view. 29. Pierella lamia; 30. Pierella chalybaea stat. rest.; 31. Pierella boliviana stat. nov.; 32. Pierella angeloi sp. nov.; 33. Pierella kesselringi sp. nov.; 34. Pierella nice sp. nov.; 35. Pierella keithbrowni sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267358/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="373">
Fig. 
<number box="[1152,1183,1946,1970]" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tegumen is dorsally larger than in 
<taxonomicName box="[307,398,1981,2006]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pierella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamia">
<emphasis box="[307,398,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="373">P. lamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, uncus straight and tapering at the apex, valva with apex projected out upwards and serrated with some reduced spines on sacculus, aedeagus rounded at the anterior portion (
<figureCitation box="[1066,1198,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 47" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1466,1489]" captionTargetBox="[170,1429,450,1415]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,409,1445]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 47. Male genitalia of “ Pierella lamia species group ”. 36 – 41. Pierella lamia: 36. lateral; 37. dorsal; 38. ventral; 39. valva, inner view; 40. aedeagus, lateral; 41. aedeagus, dorsal. 42 – 47. Pierella boliviana stat. nov.: 42. lateral; 43. dorsal; 44. ventral; 45. valva, inner view; 46. aedeagus, lateral; 47. aedeagus, dorsal. Scales bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267359/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="374">
Figs 
<number box="[1123,1198,152,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="374" value="44.5" valueMax="47.0" valueMin="42.0">42–47</number>
</figureCitation>
). In female genitalia, the papillae anales have a developed and curved posterior aphophysis similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1056,1168,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Pierella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angeloi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1056,1168,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="374">P. angeloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1176,1266,188,213]" pageId="8" pageNumber="374" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1176,1266,188,213]" pageId="8" pageNumber="374">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, corpus bursae almost the same length of ductus bursae, and with a paired signa on the ventral side (
<figureCitation box="[1101,1232,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 61" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1801,1824]" captionTargetBox="[157,1435,226,1770]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1780]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 61. Female genitalia of “ Pierella lamia species group ”. 48 – 49. Pierella lamia: 48. lateral; 49. ventral. 50 – 51. Pierella chalybaea stat. rest.: 50. lateral; 51. ventral. 52 – 53. Pierella boliviana stat. nov.: 52. lateral; 53. ventral. 54 – 55. Pierella angeloi sp. nov.: 54. lateral; 55. ventral; 56 – 57. Pierella kesselringi sp. nov.: 56. lateral; 57. ventral. 58 – 59. Pierella nice sp. nov.: 58. lateral; 59. ventral. 60 – 61. Pierella keithbrowni sp. nov.: 60. lateral; 61. ventral. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267360/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="374">
Figs 
<number box="[1157,1232,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="374" value="52.5" valueMax="53.0" valueMin="52.0">52–53</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="374" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="374">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,260,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="374">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[364,449,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 62" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1471,1493]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,553,1447]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,553,1448]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 62. Geographical distribution of “ Pierella lamia ” species group." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267361/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="374">
